main event: A UFO sighting occurred near Sherman, Texas in the summer of 1965.
interesting points: The sighting received a great deal of publicity at the time and the organization had received numerous inquiries about it since then.
The organization considered the case to be one of the more puzzling and interesting UFO reports that had come to their attention.
The handwritten document mentions a Capt. D. reporting on the sighting, which lasted for 2 hours and 3 minutes.
The document also mentions a disc-shaped object in the sky that appeared shapeless and looked like a swarm of insects.
The document mentions a plane making a U-turn and then canceling out on its ship, before returning downwards.
photographs: No photographs present in the image.
